## Problem

As part of https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab/-/issues/354480, we started triggering project statistics updates when receiving a tag creation or deletion event from the container registry. This was done in https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab/-/merge_requests/85108.

In https://gitlab.com/gitlab-com-top-initiatives/free-saas-user-efficiency/free-saas/-/issues/93#note_1026424298, we have now identified that we're missing one event: manifest deletions.

Deleting a manifest on the new registry is a DB cascading operation that will also delete any tags. However, because the tag deletion happens behind the scenes on the DB, there is no tag delete event emitted in this situation. As result, a project's cached registry usage is not updated when a manifest is deleted. This is critical for active repositories (as soon there will be a tag creation/deletion event that will fix the out-of-sync project usage), but if the manifest being deleted is the last one on the repository, there will be no more events for that repository and we're stuck with a non-zero cached project usage on the Rails side forever.

## Solution

In https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab/-/merge_requests/85108/diffs#291d6eaf4f8480001607e173f9402fb4dde7156a_63_77 we skip processing registry events if they don't target a tag. We need to change this. We should also process a delete event when there is no `target.tag` field in the payload, just a `target.digest`.

Sample manifest delete event payload:

```json
{
    "events": [
        {
            "id": "fe702f5b-4e46-4f82-abd8-f40047930dc2",
            "timestamp": "2022-07-14T12:18:45.019877+01:00",
            "action": "delete",
            "target": {
                "digest": "sha256:a777c9c66ba177ccfea23f2a216ff6721e78a662cd17019488c417135299cd89",
                "repository": "new/repo"
            },
            "request": {
                "id": "f20013f5-0543-4991-89bf-058c228ceaaf",
                "addr": "172.16.123.1:61829",
                "host": "172.16.123.1:5000",
                "method": "DELETE",
                "useragent": "HTTPie/3.2.1"
            },
            "actor": {},
            "source": {
                "addr": "Joaos-MBP-GitLab.local:5000",
                "instanceID": "d063c416-d185-456f-8fd3-e94d13fed32c"
            }
        }
    ]
}
```

## Overview

Use this issue to discuss and define a [JSONSchema](https://json-schema.org/) that will describe each audit event type.

The definition of done for this issue should be:

- Documenting the new schema in our audit event guide.
- Create a few example type definitions.

## Initial proposal

I've defined an example first JSON schema. Please give feedback on thoughts/changed/additions/removals!

```json
{
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-06/schema#",
  "$ref": "#/definitions/GitLabAuditEventType",
  "definitions": {
    "GitLabAuditEventType": {
      "type": "object",
      "additionalProperties": false,
      "properties": {
        "name": {
          "type": "string",
          "description": "Unique identifying name for the type of audit event"
        },
        "description": {
          "type": "string",
          "description": "A human-readable description of how this event is triggered"
        },
        "introduced_by_issue": {
          "type": "string",
          "format": "uri",
          "description": "URL to GitLab issue that added this type of audit event",
          "qt-uri-protocols": [
            "https"
          ]
        },
        "introduced_by_mr": {
          "type": "string",
          "format": "uri",
          "description": "URL to GitLab merge request that added this type of audit event",
          "qt-uri-protocols": [
            "https"
          ]
        },
        "engineering_group": {
          "type": "string",
          "description": "Name of the group that introduced this audit event. e.g. manage::compliance"
        },
        "milestone": {
          "type": "number",
          "description": "Milestone that introduced this audit event type, e.g. 15.8"
        },
        "saved_to_database": {
          "type": "boolean",
          "description": "Should events of this type be persisted to the database and JSON logs?"
        },
        "streamed": {
          "type": "boolean",
          "description": "Should events of this type be streamed to external services? (where configured)"
        }
      },
      "required": [
        "description",
        "engineering_group",
        "introduced_by_issue",
        "introduced_by_mr",
        "milestone",
        "name",
        "saved_to_database",
        "streamed"
      ],
      "title": "GitLabAuditEventType"
    }
  }
}
```
